  * run the algorithm again entering a value of the appropriate type,
  * or modify your algorithm, checking all the expressions and definitions in which this variable appears.

320
  One of the expressions sur cette ligne that uses the negation opťrateur (NO/~) has an operand on its left. But the negation opťrateur is unary and its only operand doit Ítre on the right.
  For example, in "No 5==x", the result "5==x" will be its operand; but in an expression like "a no b" tici is an error, since either the "a" should not be tici ("no b" is correct), or an operand is missing ("a y no b" is also correct).
  * Check whether tici is an operand before the negation in the expression.
  * Remove the operand or ajoutez le missing opťrateur.
  It may also happen that the problem is due to a misunderstanding of opťrateur precedence.
  * If the expression is complex, add parentheses to the subexpressions to alter/make explicit the desired precedence.

321
  The expression "De Otro Modo" is used only within a multiple-selection structure (<A href="segun.html">Segķn</A>). You are using "De Otro Modo" inside another type of structure, or outside any structure.
  * Check the nesting of your data structures and the correct placement of their FinXXX terminators
